headline: Super Micro (SMCI) Is Up 14.9% After Deepening AI Partnership With AMD and Expanding Server Portfolio
summary: This past week, AMD announced a major multiyear partnership to supply OpenAI with advanced AI chips, prompting renewed interest in server providers like Super Micro Computer, which serves as a key OEM partner by integrating AMD’s CPUs and GPUs into its high-performance server solutions. Super Micro has just launched a new lineup of AI-optimized computing systems featuring the latest GPUs from both AMD and Nvidia, highlighting its focus on rapid product innovation and strengthening its role...

headline: The AI Bubble Is Here. 9 Stocks to Play It.
summary: Seaport Global analyst Jay  Goldberg is firmly in the bubble camp.  While chips are a critical part of the AI chain, he’s not sure that the business cycles are synced: “So saying that ASML,  Applied Materials Lam Research  and  KLA  are AI stories is a bit of stretch, but AI is definitely one of many important drivers of their business.”
